  "texts": [
    "This suggests that employing a representative design approach is valuable for evaluating laypeople's self-triage performance with and without SAAs.",
    "Importantly, we do not claim that the sampling method presented in this article is or should be the only and best way to evaluate SAAs.",
    "On the contrary, in line with the concept of representative design, we suggest that each use case requires its specific set of stimuli (e.g., case vignettes sampled from different populations in specific situations).",
    "For example, to identify if SAAs miss severe cases with atypical clinical presentations, vignettes should only be sampled from patients that presented with atypical symptoms.",
    "In this sense, also traditional vignettes can provide valuable insights, for instance, to examine how SAAs might perform when being used by clinicians."
  ],
